  <article class="container-prose prose-editorial cs-body" set:html={`<h3><b>Educational Case Study Disclosure</b></h3><p>This case study is hypothetical and for educational purposes only. Scenarios, borrower profiles, loan terms, interest rates, and outcomes are illustrative examples and do not represent current offers or guaranteed terms.</p><p>For specific details including down payment requirements, closing cost estimates, interest rate details, closing cost breakdowns, payment calculations, cash-to-close estimates, or an official Loan Estimate, it is highly recommended you<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a meeting with one of our licensed mortgage advisors</a>.</p><p><b>Learn more:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/24/">Stated income loan refinance Reg Z advertising requirements (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB official regulation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1026">Stated income loan refinance Reg Z full text and compliance</a> – Electronic Code of Federal Regulations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/interp-24/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official stated income loan refinance advertising interpretations (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB interpretations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1014" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stated income loan refinance MAP Rule (Reg N) mortgage advertising</a> – Mortgage advertising rules</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/">NMLS Consumer Access – Verify stated income loan refinance lender licensure</a></li></ul><p>Actual loan terms vary by credit profile, property, occupancy, location, market conditions, and lender guidelines. For current options tailored to you,<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>.</p><p>Ready to explore your options?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor.</p>		
					<h2>How Did Stated Income Loan Refinance Lower This Business Owner's Payment?</h2>				
		<p>Carlos M., a 39-year-old restaurant owner in Miami, had built two successful restaurants over the past decade—an upscale Latin fusion concept in Brickell and a casual family-style restaurant in Coral Gables. His business income came from multiple sources: S-corporation distributions, consulting fees from menu development work with other restaurants, partnership income from a food truck venture, and occasional income from culinary events and private catering. Despite generating strong six-figure income from his combined ventures, Carlos's tax returns showed substantially reduced income due to legitimate business deductions for equipment, ingredients, marketing, and other operational expenses.</p><p>Several years ago, Carlos had purchased his primary residence using a conventional mortgage when interest rates were significantly higher. Now, with rates having dropped substantially and his home having appreciated significantly, refinancing made perfect financial sense. The monthly savings would be substantial, improving his cash flow and allowing him to invest more capital back into expanding his restaurant operations.</p><p>What Carlos didn't anticipate was that traditional lenders would be unable to refinance his mortgage due to the same complex income documentation challenges that had made his original purchase difficult. Despite having paid every mortgage payment on time for years, maintaining excellent credit, and clearly earning strong income from his successful restaurants, conventional lenders couldn't calculate his qualifying income from his complex business structure.</p><p>Facing similar challenges?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to explore your options.</p><h2><b>The Challenge: Why Traditional Lenders Couldn't Refinance Despite Perfect Payment History</b></h2><p>Carlos contacted three conventional mortgage lenders expecting straightforward refinance approval. He had substantial equity in his home from appreciation, excellent credit maintained over years of on-time payments, and strong business income from his thriving restaurants. Every lender rejected his refinance application within days.</p><h3><b>Why Do Traditional Lenders Reject Stated Income Loan Refinance for Self-Employed Borrowers?</b></h3><p>Traditional mortgage lenders follow the same rigid income documentation requirements for refinancing as they do for purchase loans—even when borrowers have proven their ability to handle mortgage payments through years of perfect payment history. These lenders must calculate qualifying income using tax return formulas that often dramatically understate actual earnings for business owners who structure their finances for tax efficiency.</p><p>For refinances, this creates an absurd situation: borrowers who have successfully paid their mortgages for years can't refinance to better terms because their tax returns don't show sufficient income—even though they've clearly demonstrated the ability to afford the payment by making it successfully for years.</p><h3><b>What Made Carlos's Income Too Complex for Conventional Refinancing?</b></h3><p>Carlos's income documentation presented multiple challenges for traditional lenders:</p><p><b>Complex business income structure:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">S-corporation distributions from two restaurant entities</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Consulting income paid as 1099 from menu development work</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Partnership K-1 income from food truck venture</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Variable catering and event income throughout the year</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Income spread across multiple tax schedules and forms</li></ul><p><b>Tax return complications:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Substantial business deductions reducing taxable income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Depreciation of restaurant equipment and vehicles</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Marketing and advertising expenses across multiple entities</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Food cost deductions and operational expenses</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Business reinvestment reducing reported personal income</li></ul><p>"I've paid my mortgage on time for years without a single late payment," Carlos explained. "My restaurants generate strong consistent income, I have excellent credit, and I want to refinance to a lower rate—not borrow more money. But traditional lenders treated my refinance request as if I was a brand new borrower, requiring me to prove my income all over again using tax returns that don't show my true earning capacity."</p><h3><b>How Did Tax-Efficient Business Structure Prevent Rate Reduction?</b></h3><p>Carlos's accountant had structured his restaurants to minimize tax liability through legitimate business deductions—smart financial management that reduced his tax burden but made traditional mortgage qualification nearly impossible.</p><p><b>Carlos's actual financial situation:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Strong monthly cash flow from two successful restaurants</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Years of perfect mortgage payment history proving affordability</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Excellent credit score maintained consistently</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Significant equity from home appreciation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Conservative lifestyle with minimal personal debt</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Clear ability to afford current payment (and would benefit from lower payment)</li></ul><p><b>How traditional lenders saw Carlos's situation:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Complicated tax returns with income from multiple sources</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Business deductions reducing calculated qualifying income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Income that appeared lower than when he originally purchased</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Complex underwriting requiring weeks of documentation analysis</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Risk of denial despite perfect payment history</li></ul><p>"My accountant does exactly what he should—minimize my taxes legally," Carlos said. "But that tax efficiency makes refinancing impossible through traditional lenders. I'm not asking to borrow more money or increase my payment risk. I just want to lower my rate and payment on a mortgage I've paid perfectly for years. But traditional lenders couldn't look past my tax returns to see that obvious reality."</p><h3><b>Why Couldn't Conventional Lenders Consider Payment History?</b></h3><p>Traditional mortgage underwriting focuses almost exclusively on calculated qualifying income from tax returns, giving little weight to actual demonstrated payment history. While a perfect payment record proves borrower reliability, conventional formulas still require income calculation from tax documentation—creating an impossible barrier for business owners whose tax returns understate their true earnings.</p><p>"It felt insane," Carlos reflected. "I've proven I can afford this mortgage by paying it successfully for years. But traditional lenders said my tax returns don't show enough income to qualify for refinancing to a lower payment than I'm already making successfully. The system is completely backwards for self-employed borrowers."</p><p>Experiencing similar rejection?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to discuss alternative qualification methods.</p><h2><b>The Discovery: How Carlos Found Stated Income Loan Refinance Programs</b></h2><p>Carlos discovered<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/stated-income-loan"> stated income loan refinance</a> programs through his commercial banker who worked with many restaurant owners facing similar challenges. The banker explained that stated income lenders verify income through bank statements and overall financial strength rather than complex tax return calculations—particularly valuable for refinances where payment history already proves affordability.</p><p>"My banker said stated income refinance programs focus on whether I actually earn the income I claim by looking at bank deposits, not by trying to calculate income from complicated tax returns," Carlos explained. "For refinances especially, they consider my perfect payment history as strong evidence I can afford the mortgage—which makes so much more sense than ignoring years of successful payments."</p><h3><b>What Makes Stated Income Loan Refinance Different from Traditional Refinancing?</b></h3><p>The stated income loan advisor explained that stated income refinance programs evaluate borrowers through bank statement income verification, asset documentation, credit history, and—critically for refinances—existing mortgage payment history rather than rigid tax return income formulas.</p><p><b>Stated income loan refinance advantages for self-employed borrowers:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Income verified through bank deposits, not tax return calculations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Existing payment history considered as evidence of affordability</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Bank statement analysis shows actual cash flow patterns</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Asset verification demonstrates financial stability</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Overall financial profile evaluated comprehensively</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">No need to explain every line item on complex business tax returns</li></ul><p>"The stated income loan refinance approach made perfect sense," Carlos said. "They verified that I actually earn strong income by reviewing consistent deposits into my bank accounts from my restaurants. They saw my perfect mortgage payment history proving I can afford the payment. They confirmed I have excellent credit and substantial assets. That complete picture showed I was an excellent refinance candidate—far better than trying to calculate my income from tax returns that my accountant structures to minimize taxes."</p><h3><b>How Do Stated Income Lenders Evaluate Refinance Applications?</b></h3><p>The stated income loan advisor reviewed Carlos's complete refinancing profile:</p><p><b>Payment history verification:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Years of perfect mortgage payment history</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">No late payments or delinquencies on any obligations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Demonstrated successful homeownership and financial responsibility</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Clear evidence of ability to afford existing payment</li></ul><p><b>Bank statement income verification:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Multiple months of business bank statements showing revenue</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Personal bank statements showing consistent deposits from businesses</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Cash flow patterns demonstrating strong regular income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Verification that claimed income matches actual deposits</li></ul><p><b>Financial strength documentation:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Excellent credit scores maintained over years</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Substantial home equity from appreciation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Additional assets demonstrating financial stability</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Conservative debt levels relative to assets and income</li></ul><p>"The stated income lender looked at the complete picture," Carlos explained. "My perfect payment history, my bank statements showing strong consistent income, my excellent credit, and my substantial equity all told the same story—I'm a responsible borrower who can easily afford refinancing to a lower rate. That holistic evaluation captured my true financial situation far better than focusing solely on tax return income calculations."</p><h2><b>The Solution: Stated Income Loan Refinance Approval Process</b></h2><p>Carlos worked with his stated income loan advisor to compile documentation that verified his income through bank statements and demonstrated his financial strength through payment history and asset documentation.</p><h3><b>What Documentation Did Carlos Provide for Stated Income Loan Refinance Approval?</b></h3><p>Stated income loan refinance requires comprehensive documentation verifying income and financial capacity through alternative methods:</p><p><b>Payment history documentation:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Mortgage payment history showing years of on-time payments</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Current mortgage statement with payment amount and balance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Evidence of payments through bank statements or servicer records</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Payment history on all other obligations demonstrating responsibility</li></ul><p><b>Bank statement income verification:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Extended months of business bank statements from both restaurants</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Personal bank statements showing deposits from business operations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Verification of consistent cash flow patterns and income sources</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Documentation demonstrating regular strong income deposits</li></ul><p><b>Asset and equity documentation:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Current home appraisal showing substantial appreciation and equity</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Investment account statements demonstrating liquid reserves</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Business account balances confirming operational financial strength</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Overall net worth documentation supporting financial stability</li></ul><p><b>Credit and business verification:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Credit reports from all bureaus showing excellent scores</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Business licenses and entity documentation for both restaurants</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Evidence of ongoing successful restaurant operations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Professional credentials and industry reputation</li></ul><p><b>Refinance transaction documentation:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Current mortgage balance and terms</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Desired refinance structure and objectives</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Property insurance and other requirements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Evidence of ability to cover closing costs</li></ul><p>"The documentation process focused on proving what I actually earn through bank deposits rather than explaining complicated tax returns," Carlos said. "I provided bank statements from my restaurants showing consistent strong revenue, my mortgage payment history proving years of successful payments, and my credit reports showing excellent scores. The stated income lender verified my income through actual deposits and my reliability through payment history—a much more accurate assessment than tax return formulas."</p><h3><b>How Long Does Stated Income Loan Refinance Take?</b></h3><p>The stated income lender moved efficiently through Carlos's refinance application:</p><ol><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Initial consultation</b> - Reviewed refinance goals and income situation (Day 1)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Preliminary approval</b> - Confirmed stated income loan refinance would work (Day 3)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Document submission</b> - Uploaded bank statements, payment history, credit reports (Day 5-7)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Payment history verification</b> - Confirmed years of perfect payments (Day 8-10)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Bank statement analysis</b> - Verified income through deposit patterns (Day 10-14)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Credit and asset review</b> - Confirmed excellent credit and substantial equity (Day 12-15)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Property appraisal</b> - Home appraised confirming strong equity position (Day 15-21)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Underwriting approval</b> - Approved based on complete financial profile (Day 22)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Clear to close</b> - Final approval issued (Day 28)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Closing</b> - Successfully refinanced with lower rate (Day 35)</li></ol><h3><b>What Terms Did the Stated Income Loan Refinance Provide?</b></h3><p>Carlos secured stated income loan refinance terms that delivered the monthly savings he sought:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Favorable interest rate</b> significantly lower than existing mortgage</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Competitive rate structure</b> for stated income loan refinance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Long-term fixed-rate mortgage</b> maintaining payment stability</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Substantial monthly payment reduction</b> improving cash flow</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>No prepayment penalties</b> allowing future refinancing flexibility</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Standard amortization</b> continuing principal reduction efficiently</li></ul><p>"The stated income loan refinance delivered exactly what I needed," Carlos explained. "The rate was substantially lower than my existing mortgage, the monthly payment reduction was significant, and the long-term fixed structure gave me payment predictability. Most importantly, the approval process took weeks rather than months of trying to explain my complex business tax returns to conventional underwriters who would likely have denied me anyway."</p><p>Exploring refinance?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/refinance-or-heloc-inquiry/"> Submit a refinance inquiry</a> to compare your options.</p><h2><b>The Results: Substantial Monthly Savings and Improved Cash Flow</b></h2><p>Carlos closed his stated income loan refinance approximately five weeks after starting the application. The improved terms delivered immediate monthly savings that he reinvested into his restaurant operations and long-term business growth.</p><h3><b>What Results Did Carlos Achieve with Stated Income Loan Refinance?</b></h3><p><b>Final refinancing outcome:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Successfully refinanced existing mortgage to substantially lower rate</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Competitive interest rate for stated income loan refinance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Long-term fixed-rate structure maintaining stability</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Substantial monthly payment reduction</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Timeline:</b> Application to closing in 35 days</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Property:</b> Primary residence, Miami, FL</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Perfect payment history preserved and rewarded</b></li></ul><p><b>Financial impact after refinancing:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Significant monthly payment reduction improving personal cash flow</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Savings reinvested into restaurant expansion and marketing</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Continued building equity through appreciation and principal paydown</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Improved financial flexibility for business investments</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Maintained excellent credit through refinancing process</li></ul><h3><b>How Did Stated Income Loan Refinance Compare to Traditional Attempts?</b></h3><p><b>Traditional lender attempts vs. stated income loan refinance:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Traditional lender qualification:</b> Rejected due to complex income documentation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Stated income lender qualification:</b> Approved through bank statement verification</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Payment history consideration:</b> Traditional ignored it; stated income valued it</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Documentation burden:</b> Traditional required explaining tax returns; stated income used bank statements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Timeline:</b> Traditional uncertain and lengthy; stated income completed in 35 days</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Monthly savings achieved:</b> Stated income loan refinance made it possible</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Refinancing goal:</b> ACHIEVED ✓</li></ul><p>"The stated income loan refinance saved me substantial money monthly while requiring far less documentation hassle than traditional refinancing," Carlos said. "I've been paying this mortgage successfully for years, proving I can afford it. The stated income lender recognized that payment history, verified my income through bank deposits showing my restaurants generate strong revenue, and approved my refinance quickly. Now I have a much lower payment, better cash flow, and I'm reinvesting the savings into growing my businesses."</p><h3><b>What Are Carlos's Next Steps After Successful Refinance?</b></h3><p>The monthly savings from Carlos's stated income loan refinance provide additional capital he's using to expand his restaurant operations. He's considering opening a third location, investing in kitchen equipment upgrades, and expanding his catering operations—all growth initiatives that will increase his business revenue and long-term wealth.</p><p>"The refinance savings give me breathing room to invest more aggressively in my businesses," Carlos explained. "Lower monthly payments mean more cash flow I can deploy into revenue-generating activities. I'm also considering purchasing investment real estate once I'm ready to diversify beyond my restaurant businesses—building wealth across multiple asset classes rather than keeping everything in the restaurant industry."</p><p>When Carlos is ready to pursue real estate investing, he may use stated income loan programs again for their documentation simplicity, or potentially explore<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/dscr-loan"> DSCR Loans</a> that eliminate personal income verification entirely for investment properties. He's also considering using a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc"> HELOC</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/home-equity-loan"> Home Equity Loan</a> to access his substantial home equity for business expansion or investment property down payments.</p><p>"The stated income loan refinance experience taught me that alternative documentation programs recognize the reality of self-employed finances better than traditional lenders," Carlos reflected. "My tax returns don't tell my complete financial story because they're structured for tax efficiency. Stated income lenders understand that and verify income through actual bank deposits instead. Now I have lower monthly payments, better cash flow, and proven financing options I can use again for future financial goals."</p><p>Ready to get started?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your situation.</p><h2><b>Exploring Other Stated Income Loan Options?</b></h2><p>While Carlos used stated income loan refinance to reduce his rate, stated income financing works for multiple scenarios:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Want to access equity? See how a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-cash-out-refinance"> business owner used stated income loan cash-out refinance to expand operations</a></li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Purchasing investment property? Learn how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-purchase"> entrepreneur used stated income loan for property acquisition</a></li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> to find success stories matching your situation</li></ul><h2><b>Key Takeaways for Self-Employed Borrowers Seeking to Refinance</b></h2><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Stated income loan refinance programs verify income through bank deposits rather than tax return calculations</b>—particularly valuable for self-employed borrowers whose tax returns understate actual earnings due to legitimate business deductions and tax-efficient structures (<a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/">Understanding alternative documentation mortgages</a>)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Perfect payment history proves affordability better than tax return formulas</b>—stated income refinance lenders consider years of successful mortgage payments as strong evidence of ability to afford refinanced payments, unlike traditional lenders who focus solely on calculated income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Bank statement analysis captures true earning capacity</b>—consistent deposits from business operations into bank accounts demonstrate actual income far more accurately than tax returns structured to minimize tax liability</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Stated income loan refinance requires strong financial profiles</b>—excellent credit, substantial equity, significant reserves, and verifiable income through bank deposits are essential; these programs serve qualified borrowers with complex documentation, not subprime borrowers (<a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/">Mortgage lending regulations</a>)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Refinancing savings can accelerate business growth and wealth building</b>—lower monthly payments improve cash flow that can be reinvested into business expansion, real estate investing, or other wealth-building activities rather than being trapped in higher-rate mortgages due to documentation challenges</li></ul><p>Have questions about stated income loan refinance for complex income situations?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor today.</p><h2><b>Alternative Loan Programs for Self-Employed Refinancing</b></h2><p>If stated income loan refinance isn't the perfect fit, consider these alternatives:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/bank-statement-loan">Bank Statement Loan</a> – Refinance using bank deposits rather than tax returns</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan">Asset-Based Loan</a> – Qualify using liquid assets rather than income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/1099-loan">1099 Loan</a> – For 1099 contractors with income documentation challenges</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/profit-loss-loan">P&amp;L Loan (Profit and Loss)</a> – Qualify using CPA-prepared profit and loss statements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/portfolio-loan">Portfolio Loan</a> – Flexible refinancing for unique situations</li></ul><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">Explore all loan programs</a> to find your best refinancing solution.</p><h2><b>Helpful Stated Income Loan Refinance Resources</b></h2><p><b>Learn more about this loan program:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/stated-income-loan">Complete Stated Income Loan Guide</a> - Detailed requirements, rates, and qualification guidelines</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/stated-income-loan-calculator">Stated Income Loan Calculator</a> - Estimate your refinancing savings</li></ul><p><b>Similar success stories:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-cash-out-refinance">How a business owner used stated income loan cash-out refinance for expansion</a> - Accessing equity success</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-purchase">Entrepreneur purchases investment property with stated income loan</a> - Alternative documentation purchase</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> - Browse by your situation</li></ul><p><b>External authoritative resources:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/">Understanding alternative documentation mortgages</a> - Consumer Financial Protection Bureau guidance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/">Mortgage lending regulations</a> - Federal lending standards</li></ul><p><b>Ready to get started?</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Apply online</a> - Start your refinance application</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a consultation</a> - Discuss your refinancing goals</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/">Take the discovery quiz</a> - Clarify your needs</li></ul><p>Need local expertise?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/get-a-local-introduction/"> Get introduced to trusted partners</a> including CPAs specializing in small business owners, financial advisors, and mortgage professionals who understand self-employed finances.</p>		
